title: koryu
author: koryu
content: Hi,I am looking for help to price check this rare LEALANA Set #253 from 2013 with Black Address and tagged "Buyer Funded" while the coins are not funded.The coins never left their capsules and were bought first hand from smoothie long ago. The capsules have some scatches. I got all public keys for the coins.Any help is appreciated.Best regards~koryups: I am not selling these coins anywhere, dont trust any impersonators.

comments.author: CoinageMint
comments.body: Not much help with pricing, but you may find this thread interesting: https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=5415111.msg61019629#msg61019629

comments.author: Cryptogreatdane
comments.body: My humble opinion- so first consider where you sell. You will get more on ebay or even the new stacks and bauer auctions. Coins on forum tend to sell cheaper. Also you will get much more if you wait till btc on the upswing again. Brings out more buyers. If you sold now id say break them up and sell individually as sad as that is. So on ebay the 1 btc sold at auction for around 4500 in early summer. But a current coin has been stuck at 5000 for awhile now. The other 3 coins sell for between 2000-3000 each. Now that being said stacks sold that funded 0.1 last Nov for 33k. So really it just comes down to exposure to right buyers. If you wait these will be worth much more in the future. But heres my best guess what youll get if you soldEbay as a group- 6-8Ebay individual- 10-12Forum- 3-4 but sell quick

comments.author: Hox
comments.body: A similar 4 coin set was recently sold on ebay for $9600 USD.That set included signed COA's, but the serial numbers didn't all match like your set, so I would say your set is worth around this much, maybe a little less.
